	<Text>he Mention-in-Despatches (MID) is the longest continuous British gallantry award for military personnel. It was awarded for acts which were judged of sufficient merit to be officially mentioned in the despatches sent by the officer, commanding a theatre of operation, back to the War Office in London.</Text>
